a type of meat that's produced using tissue engineering techniques traditio=
nally used in regenerative medicine. The process, and the scientific advanc=
ements that make it possible, is why Not Boring&#8217;s Elliot Hershberg th=
inks we&#8217;re not too far off from being able to grow </span><em>anythin=
g </em><span>in a lab.</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16p=
